The paper discusses the use of machine learning for drug discovery, specifically in virtual screening. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of pre-trained language models from natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed method involves learning molecular fingerprints through unsupervised pre-training, which is a machine learning technique and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a novel metric to measure model accuracy and data efficiency, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and computer engineering (cs.CE), respectively. Overall, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.CL, followed by cs.CE, cs.CV, and cs.AI.
